106/** Proxy class that allows verification on GWorld accesses. */
107class UWorldProxy
108{
109public:
110
111 UWorldProxy() :
112 World(NULL)
113 {}
114
115 inline UWorld* operator->()
116 {
117 // GWorld is changed often on the game thread when in PIE, accessing on any other thread is going to be a race condition
118 // In general, the rendering thread should not dereference UObjects, unless there is a mechanism in place to make it safe
119 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
120 return World;
121 }
122
123 inline const UWorld* operator->() const
124 {
125 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
126 return World;
127 }
128
129 inline UWorld& operator*()
130 {
131 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
132 return *World;
133 }
134
135 inline const UWorld& operator*() const
136 {
137 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
138 return *World;
139 }
140
141 inline UWorldProxy& operator=(UWorld* InWorld)
142 {
143 World = InWorld;
144 return *this;
145 }
146
147 inline UWorldProxy& operator=(const UWorldProxy& InProxy)
148 {
149 World = InProxy.World;
150 return *this;
151 }
152
153 inline bool operator==(const UWorldProxy& Other) const
154 {
155 return World == Other.World;
156 }
157
158 inline operator UWorld*() const
159 {
160 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
161 return World;
162 }
163
164 inline UWorld* GetReference()
165 {
166 checkSlow(IsInGameThread());
167 return World;
168 }
169
170private:
171
172 UWorld* World;
173};

192/** class that encapsulates seamless world traveling */
193class FSeamlessTravelHandler
194{
195private:
196 /** URL we're traveling to */
197 FURL PendingTravelURL;
198 /** set to the loaded package once loading is complete. Transition to it is performed in the next tick where it's safe to perform the required operations */
199 UObject* LoadedPackage;
200 /** the world we are travelling from */
201 UWorld* CurrentWorld;
202 /** set to the loaded world object inside that package. This is added to the root set (so that if a GC gets in between it won't break loading) */
203 UWorld* LoadedWorld;
204 /** set when a transition is in progress */
205 bool bTransitionInProgress;
206 /** whether or not we've transitioned to the entry level and are now moving on to the specified map */
207 bool bSwitchedToDefaultMap;
208 /** while set, pause at midpoint (after loading transition level, before loading final destination) */
209 bool bPauseAtMidpoint;
210 /** set when we started a new travel in the middle of a previous one and still need to clean up that previous attempt */
211 bool bNeedCancelCleanUp;
212 /** The context we are running in. Can be used to get the FWorldContext from Engine*/
213 FName WorldContextHandle;
214 /** Real time which we started traveling at */
215 double SeamlessTravelStartTime = 0.0;
216
217 /** copy data between the old world and the new world */
218 void CopyWorldData();
219
220 /** callback sent to async loading code to inform us when the level package is complete */
221 void SeamlessTravelLoadCallback(const FName& PackageName, UPackage* LevelPackage, EAsyncLoadingResult::Type Result);
222
223 void SetHandlerLoadedData(UObject* InLevelPackage, UWorld* InLoadedWorld);
224
225 /** Wrapper for loading transition or destination map, returns false if not found */
226 bool StartLoadingMap(FString MapPackageToLoadFrom);
227
228 /** called to kick off async loading of the destination map and any other packages it requires */
229 void StartLoadingDestination();
230
231public:
232 FSeamlessTravelHandler()
233 : PendingTravelURL(NoInit)
234 , LoadedPackage(NULL)
235 , CurrentWorld(NULL)
236 , LoadedWorld(NULL)
237 , bTransitionInProgress(false)
238 , bSwitchedToDefaultMap(false)
239 , bPauseAtMidpoint(false)
240 , bNeedCancelCleanUp(false)
241 {}
242
243 /** starts traveling to the given URL. The required packages will be loaded async and Tick() will perform the transition once we are ready
244 * @param InURL the URL to travel to
245 * @return whether or not we succeeded in starting the travel
246 */
247 bool StartTravel(UWorld* InCurrentWorld, const FURL& InURL);
248
249 /** @return whether a transition is already in progress */
250 FORCEINLINE bool IsInTransition() const
251 {
252 return bTransitionInProgress;
253 }
254 /** @return if current transition has switched to the default map; returns false if no transition is in progress */
255 FORCEINLINE bool HasSwitchedToDefaultMap() const
256 {
257 return IsInTransition() && bSwitchedToDefaultMap;
258 }
259
260 /** @return the destination map that is being travelled to via seamless travel */
261 inline FString GetDestinationMapName() const
262 {
263 return (IsInTransition() ? PendingTravelURL.Map : TEXT(""));
264 }
265
266 /** @return the destination world that has been loaded asynchronously by the seamless travel handler. */
267 inline const UWorld* GetLoadedWorld() const
268 {
269 return LoadedWorld;
270 }
271
272 /** cancels transition in progress */
273 void CancelTravel();
274
275 /** turns on/off pausing after loading the transition map
276 * only valid during travel, before we've started loading the final destination
277 * @param bNowPaused - whether the transition should now be paused
278 */
279 void SetPauseAtMidpoint(bool bNowPaused);
280
281 /**
282 * Ticks the transition; handles performing the world switch once the required packages have been loaded
283 *
284 * @returns The new primary world if the world has changed, null if it has not
285 */
286 ENGINE_API UWorld* Tick();
287};

323 , CamOrthoZoom(InCamOrthoZoom)
324 , CamUpdated(false)
325 {
326 }
327
328 // Needed for backwards compatibility for VER_UE4_ADD_EDITOR_VIEWS, can be removed along with it
329 friend FArchive& operator<<( FArchive& Ar, FLevelViewportInfo& I )
330 {
331 Ar << I.CamPosition;
332 Ar << I.CamRotation;
333 Ar << I.CamOrthoZoom;
334
335 if ( Ar.IsLoading() )
336 {
337 I.CamUpdated = true;
338
339 if ( I.CamOrthoZoom < MIN_ORTHOZOOM || I.CamOrthoZoom > MAX_ORTHOZOOM )
340 {
341 I.CamOrthoZoom = DEFAULT_ORTHOZOOM;
342 }
343 }
344
345 return Ar;
346 }

472 /* Determines whether spawning will not fail if certain conditions are not met. If true, spawning will not fail because the class being spawned is `bStatic=true` or because the class of the template Actor is not the same as the class of the Actor being spawned. */
473 uint8 bNoFail:1;

496 enum class ESpawnActorNameMode : uint8

499 Required_Fatal,

505 Required_ReturnNull,
506
507 /* If the supplied Name is already in use the generate an unused one using the supplied version as a base */
508 Requested

512 ESpawnActorNameMode NameMode;
513
514 /* Flags used to describe the spawned actor/object instance. */
515 EObjectFlags ObjectFlags;
516
517 /* Custom function allowing the caller to specific a function to execute post actor construction but before other systems see this actor spawn. */

558/**
559 * This encapsulate World's async trace functionality. This contains two buffers of trace data buffer and alternates it for each tick.
560 *
561 * You can use async trace using following APIs : AsyncLineTrace, AsyncSweep, AsyncOverlap
562 * When you use those APIs, it will be saved to AsyncTraceData
563 * FWorldAsyncTraceState contains two buffers to rotate each frame as you might need the result in the next frame
564 * However, if you do not get the result by next frame, the result will be discarded.
565 * Use Delegate if you would like to get the result right away when available.
566 */
567struct FWorldAsyncTraceState
568{
569 UE_API FWorldAsyncTraceState();
570
571 /** Get the Buffer for input Frame */
572 FORCEINLINE AsyncTraceData& GetBufferForFrame (int32 Frame) { return DataBuffer[ Frame % 2]; }
573 /** Get the Buffer for Current Frame */
574 FORCEINLINE AsyncTraceData& GetBufferForCurrentFrame () { return DataBuffer[ CurrentFrame % 2]; }
575 /** Get the Buffer for Previous Frame */
576 FORCEINLINE AsyncTraceData& GetBufferForPreviousFrame() { return DataBuffer[(CurrentFrame + 1) % 2]; }
577
578 /** Async Trace Data Buffer Array. For now we only saves 2 frames. **/
579 AsyncTraceData DataBuffer[2];
580
581 /** Used as counter for Buffer swap for DataBuffer. Right now it's only 2, but it can change. */
582 int32 CurrentFrame;
583};

907/**
908 * The World is the top level object representing a map or a sandbox in which Actors and Components will exist and be rendered.
909 *
910 * A World can be a single Persistent Level with an optional list of streaming levels that are loaded and unloaded via volumes and blueprint functions
911 * or it can be a collection of levels organized with a World Composition.

913 * In a standalone game, generally only a single World exists except during seamless area transitions when both a destination and current world exists.

2352 /**
2353 * Interface for Async. Pretty much same parameter set except you can optional set delegate to be called when execution is completed and you can set UserData if you'd like
2354 * if no delegate, you can query trace data using QueryTraceData or QueryOverlapData
2355 * the data is available only in the next frame after request is made - in other words, if request is made in frame X, you can get the result in frame (X+1)
2356 *
2357 * @param InTraceType Indicates if you want multiple results, single result, or just yes/no (no hit information)
2358 * @param Start Start location of the ray
2359 * @param End End location of the ray
2360 * @param TraceChannel The 'channel' that this ray is in, used to determine which components to hit
2361 * @param Params Additional parameters used for the trace
2362 * @param ResponseParam ResponseContainer to be used for this trace
2363 * @param InDelegate Delegate function to be called - to see example, search FTraceDelegate
2364 * Example can be void MyActor::TraceDone(const FTraceHandle& TraceHandle, FTraceDatum & TraceData)
2365 * Before sending to the function,
2366 *
2367 * FTraceDelegate TraceDelegate;
2368 * TraceDelegate.BindRaw(this, &MyActor::TraceDone);
2369 *
2370 * @param UserData UserData
2371 */

3664 /**
3665 * Spawns given class and returns class T pointer, forcibly sets world transform (note this allows scale as well). WILL NOT run Construction Script of Blueprints
3666 * to give caller an opportunity to set parameters beforehand. Caller is responsible for invoking construction
3667 * manually by calling UGameplayStatics::FinishSpawningActor (see AActor::OnConstruction).
3668 */
3669 template< class T >
3670 T* SpawnActorDeferred(
3671 UClass* Class,
3672 FTransform const& Transform,
3673 AActor* Owner = nullptr,
3674 APawn* Instigator = nullptr,
3675 ESpawnActorCollisionHandlingMethod CollisionHandlingOverride = ESpawnActorCollisionHandlingMethod::Undefined,
3676 ESpawnActorScaleMethod TransformScaleMethod = ESpawnActorScaleMethod::MultiplyWithRoot
3677 )
3678 {
3679 if( Owner )
3680 {
3681 check(this==Owner->GetWorld());
3682 }
3683 FActorSpawnParameters SpawnInfo;
3684 SpawnInfo.SpawnCollisionHandlingOverride = CollisionHandlingOverride;
3685 SpawnInfo.TransformScaleMethod = TransformScaleMethod;
3686 SpawnInfo.Owner = Owner;
3687 SpawnInfo.Instigator = Instigator;
3688 SpawnInfo.bDeferConstruction = true;
3689 return (Class != nullptr) ? Cast<T>(SpawnActor(Class, &Transform, SpawnInfo)) : nullptr;
3690 }

4050 /** seamlessly travels to the given URL by first loading the entry level in the background,
4051 * switching to it, and then loading the specified level. Does not disrupt network communication or disconnect clients.
4052 * You may need to implement GameModeBase::GetSeamlessTravelActorList(), PlayerController::GetSeamlessTravelActorList(),
4053 * GameModeBase::PostSeamlessTravel(), and/or GameModeBase::HandleSeamlessTravelPlayer() to handle preserving any information
4054 * that should be maintained (player teams, etc)
4055 * This codepath is designed for worlds that use little or no level streaming and GameModes where the game state

4580FORCEINLINE_DEBUGGABLE bool UWorld::IsNetMode(ENetMode Mode) const

4584 return GetNetMode() == Mode;
4585#else
